        >
       
      </p>
      
      <h3 class="">Step Two</h3>
      <p>Once you have the above details filled. You can use three function:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <b>Replace: </b> It replace the dimension definition. Example, if the
          Segment definition had a Page Name = "Home page" dimension, you can
          change it to Page Name = "Home"
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Regex:</b> You can use Regular Expression to replace dimension
          definition.
          <b>Use double escape <code>\\ </code>for any special character</b>.
          Example, <code>"\\|help\\|click\\|\\|\\|(.*)\\|</code>
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Add and Replace</b> It will add the replaced dimension definition
          below the old one. In it, you'll have both the old and new dimension
          definition.
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p>Input to fill further:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <b>Old:</b> Input old dimension definition that you want to change
        </li>
        <li><b>New:</b> Input new dimension definition</li>
        <li>
          <b>Dimension to update</b> Input the dimension name that you want to
          change. Don't use prop or var. If prop15 = Page name, use Page name.
        </li>
      </ol>
